    <h1>Planets in the Solar System</h1>

    <h2>The Eight Planets</h2>
    <p>Based on their distance from the Sun, the eight planets of the Solar System are:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Mercury</li>
        <li>Venus</li>
        <li>Earth</li>
        <li>Mars</li>
        <li>Jupiter</li>
        <li>Saturn</li>
        <li>Uranus</li>
        <li>Neptune</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Dwarf Planets</h2>
    <p>As of mid-2008, there are five celestial bodies classified as dwarf planets:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Ceres (415 million km in the asteroid belt, known as the fifth planet)</li>
        <li>Pluto (5.906 million km, formerly classified as the ninth planet)</li>
        <li>Haumea (6.450 million km)</li>
        <li>Makemake (6.850 million km)</li>
        <li>Eris (10.100 million km)</li>
    </ul>
</body>
